{"lemma":"سِي","slug":"سِي","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"abbrev","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","prep"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21352","n21371","n21479","n21353","n21480","n21370"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"name of the Latin-script letter C, c; cee","tags":["Latin","alt-of","letter","name"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seventh note of a major scale; si"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something similar","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"هٰذَانِ سِيَّانِ.","english":"These two are similar."},{"text":"ليست «داعش» سوى ذلك الوجه من عملة فاسدة وجهها الآخر هذه الميليشيات التي تسمّي نفسها «مقاومة». هما سِيان رديفان لبعضهما وشريكان في الفعل الآثِم عينه: تمزيق العراق شعباً ووطناً ودولة والعودة به إلى تكويناته البدائية!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something equal","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"هُم سِيٌّ عِنْدِي.","english":"They are equal to me."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"similar to, like","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"هُوَ سِيُّك.","english":"He is like you."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21352","headword_ar":"سَىٌّ","root":"swY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [app. a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~N","text_ar":"سِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siy~amaA","text_ar":"لَا سِيَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21371","headword_ar":"سَىٌّ","root":"sY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~N","text_ar":"سِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swY","text_ar":"سوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see the latter in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"syw","text_ar":"سيو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21479","headword_ar":"سَىٌّ","root":"syw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swY","text_ar":"سوى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21353","headword_ar":"سِىٌّ","root":"swY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siwoYN","text_ar":"سِوْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its dual: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='N","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in ten places, all except one in the latter half of the paragraph. ―         -b2-  [Hence,] of him who is, or has become, in a state of wealth, or welfare, [or rather, of abundant wealth or welfare,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa fiY siY~i raA^osihi","text_ar":"هُوَ فِى سِىِّ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osihi","text_ar":"رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='i","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa","text_ar":"وَقَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY siY~i raA^osihi","text_ar":"فِى سِىِّ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK (erroneously)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saY~i","text_ar":"سَىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^sh","text_ar":"راسه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='i","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^sh","text_ar":"راسه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siwaA='i","text_ar":"سِوَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa","text_ar":"وَقَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^sh","text_ar":"راسه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Aln~iEomapi fiY siwaA='i","text_ar":"مِنَ النِّعْمَةِ فِى سِوَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, M,) i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has lighted upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is in the predicament of his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hukomi raA^osihi","text_ar":"حُكْمِ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in point of eminence, of wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"welfare"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what covers his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what equals his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in eminence"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yusaAwiY raA^osahu","text_ar":"يُسَاوِى رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"welfare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has equalled his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in eminence"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"welfare;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has accumulated upon him, and filled"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what equals"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the number of the hairs of his head, of wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K;) as some explain it. (A'Obeyd, S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N","text_ar":"سِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one. ―         -b3-  [Hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siy~amaA","text_ar":"لَا سِيَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA siyamaA","text_ar":"لا سِيَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", without teshdeed, (Msb, Mughnee, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA say~amaA","text_ar":"لا سَيَّمَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof, (Msb,) a compound of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~","text_ar":"سِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", denoting exception: (S:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siy~amaA zayodK","text_ar":"لَا سِيَّمَا زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA mivola","text_ar":"لَا مِثْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodK","text_ar":"زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not the like of Zeyd;"},{"kind":"text","text":"virtually, and generally, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above all Zeyd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"especially Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"being redundant: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA sy~mA","text_ar":"لا سيّما"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also; like as one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEo maA zayodN","text_ar":"دَعْ مَا زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [J says,] with respect to the case of the noun following"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":", there are two ways: you may make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY","text_ar":"الَّذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and mean that an inchoative is to be understood, [namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw","text_ar":"هو"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like,] and put the noun that you mention in the nom. case as the enunciative; thus you may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY Alqawomu laA siy~amaA A^axuwka","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى القَوْمُ لَا سِيَّمَا اَخُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siY~a Al~a*iY","text_ar":"لَا سِىَّ الَّذِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^axuwka","text_ar":"هُوَ اَخُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, came to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there was not the like of him who is thy brother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above all,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"especially, he who is thy brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA: [thus in a copy of the S: in other copies of the same, and in the TA, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~a","text_ar":"سِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siy~amaA","text_ar":"سِيَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) but this rendering is invalidated in such a phrase as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA siy~amaA zayodN","text_ar":"وَلَا سِيَّمَا زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the supression of the correlative of the noun in the nom. case where there is no lengthiness, and by the applying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"to denote a rational being: (Mughnee:) or you may put the noun after it in the gen. case, making"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"redundant, and making"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~","text_ar":"سِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to govern the noun in that case because the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~","text_ar":"سِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivol","text_ar":"مِثْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": [and this is the preferable way:] (Mughnee:) in both of these ways is recited the saying of Imra-el-Keys,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alaA rub~a yuwomK laka minohun~a SaAliHK\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA siy~amaA yawomNK bidaArapi julojuli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily many a good day was there to thee by reason of them; but there was not the like of a day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above all a day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"especially a day, at Dárat Juljul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a certain pool, where Imra-el-Keys surprised his beloved, 'Oneyzeh, with others, her companions, bathing: see EM pp. 9 and 10]: you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoribu Alqawoma walaA siy~amaA A^axiyka","text_ar":"اَضْرِبُ القَوْمَ وَلَا سِيَّمَا اَخِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA","text_ar":"وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivola Darobi A^axiyka","text_ar":"مِثْلَ ضَرْبِ اَخِيكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will beat the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, but there shall not be the like of the beating of thy brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and if you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA siy~amaA A^axuwka","text_ar":"وَلَا سِيَّمَا اَخُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA mivola Al~a*iY huwa A^axuwka","text_ar":"وَلَا مِثْلَ الَّذِى هُوَ اَخُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and there shall not be the like of him who is thy brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a fulaAnFA kariymN walaA siy~amaA A_ino A^atayotahu","text_ar":"اـِنَّ فُلَانًا كَرِيمٌ وَلَا سِيَّمَا اـِنْ اَتَيْتَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAEidFA","text_ar":"قَاعِدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Akh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for the affixed pronoun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu","text_ar":"هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is suppressed; the meaning being,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA mivolahu A_ino A^atayotahu qaAEidFA","text_ar":"وَلَا مِثْلَهُ اـِنْ اَتَيْتَهُ قَاعِدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily such a one is generous, and there is not the like of him if thou come to him sitting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) it is said in the Msb, [after explaining that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~mA","text_ar":"سيّما"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be redundant, and the noun after it governed in the gen. case as the complement of a prefixed noun; and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~*Y","text_ar":"الّذى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the noun following put in the nom. case as the enunciative of the inchoative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw","text_ar":"هو"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is suppressed;] that, accord. to some, the noun following may be in the accus. case, as being preceded by an exceptive; [or, as a specificative; (Mughnee;) in which case we must regard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a substitute for the affixed pronoun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu","text_ar":"هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1479},{"kind":"text","text":"but that this is not a good way; [and in this case, accord. to the generality of the authorities, it must be an indeterminate noun, not, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", determinate: (Mughnee:)] also that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~mA","text_ar":"سيّما"},{"kind":"text","text":"should not be used without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":"preceding it: and that it denotes the predominance of what follows it over what precedes it: but it is added that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes suppressed [as is said in the Mughnee] because known to be meant, though this is rare. (TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAsiY~a limaA fulaAnN","text_ar":"لَاسِىَّ لِمَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not the like of such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA siy~aka maA fulaAnN","text_ar":"لَا سِيَّكَ مَا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M, K) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is not the like of thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [In both of these instances,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"is obviously redundant. Other (similar) usages of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~","text_ar":"سِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaA='N","text_ar":"سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to which reference has been made above.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siY~N","text_ar":"سِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desert such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaAzap","text_ar":"مُفَازَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K) because of the evenness of its routes, and its uniformity. (TA.) [Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iY~u","text_ar":"السِّىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of a particular tract, said in the M to be a certain smooth place in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAdiyap","text_ar":"بَادِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"syw","text_ar":"سيو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Fr","S","M","K","Ks","T","TA","Msb","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n21480","headword_ar":"سِىٌّ","root":"syw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", with the compound"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siy~amaA","text_ar":"سِيَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swY","text_ar":"سوى"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Hence, perhaps, because of its uniformity, and, if so, belonging to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swY","text_ar":"سوى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaA^N siY~N","text_ar":"كَلَاٌ سِىٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant, herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by Sgh. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21370","headword_ar":"سَىْ","root":"sY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawofa","text_ar":"سَوْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}